gujarati.context:
Here is the translation:

Told at names of those who take, my name is not with me; 
Listen carefully, sins will be destroyed in the end.

This is the original couplet:

Eh aadi bhakt baibhai, sara sat sanghi gafari main;
Khatri bhakt dadoo deshaji, devbaye liha haari baje.

And here is the translation:

This is the first devotee brother, good association is found at home;
Kshatriya devotee grandfatherly, worshiped Hari with devotion.

Here is the translation:

Charan ajò rahè bagodare, bhali bhakti Prabhujiñi kare;
Bhakta bhât ādhār chhe rūdo, gajo goṛo kharo jan khodo.

Here is the translation:

Devotee of God is a good luck charm, path of heroes shines brightly; 
A devotee of hero is good fortune in adversity, the enemy's army will be burned.

Sheath naathaadi jan sundar, kaju bhakt rahe kaano tar;
Sara bhakt che shiyal maini, sheeth maado laadho ghelebhao.

(Note: I've kept the translation as close to the original couplet as possible, without adding any extra words.)

Here is the translation:

He who is a true devotee is very rare, living in his village like a wild animal; 
Many countries have many names, worshipped Hari and reached Paramdham.
